An implementation of the Broker Binary V1 format but without using
the Broker library.


The any Decoding Misery
=======================

The original Broker data format has vector, table and set as container data
types. Everything else are atomic types.



When deserializing without type information (that is, deserializing into type any),
we'll need to deserialize into table[any] of any, set[any] or vector of any, every
other variant tag can be mapped to a primitive Zeek type.

The pattern, record, func, file are represented as vectors.
